{
  "texts": [
    "After SGD converges close to a local minimum, the expected gradient norm becomes proportional to the Hessian norm and the amount of stochasticity in SGD updates, implying optimization for flatness.",
    "AveragingThe concept of using trajectory averaging for faster convergence is not novel, as evidenced by Polyak and Juditsky [91] and the literature referenced therein.",
    "However, recent research has proposed various approaches to leverage such averaging and has also clarified its correlation with generalization.",
    "Izmailov et al. [92] discovered that SGD with cyclical or constant learning rate schedules tends to converge to the vicinity of high-performing networks but often remains at the boundary rather than reaching the center.",
    "To address this, they proposed averaging the model weights from multiple points during training."
  ]
}